  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Shelter and NFI Support to Drought-Displaced Communities in Herat and Badghis Provinces</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Afghanistan Humanitarian Fund (AHF) 3rd Reserve Allocation was released after a revision of the Humanitarian Response Plan (HRP), which was revised based on a situational analysis outlining the extent of the drought emergency in the North and West of Afghanistan. Findings from needs assessments conducted in August indicate the urgent need to provide emergency shelter and Non-Food Items (NFIs), with the majority of the displaced populations living in the open and under makeshift shelters. The Reserve Allocation was therefore released to directly respond to this high priority need.

The proposed project will target drought- displaced communities in Injil District (Herat Province) Qala-e-Naw District (Badghis Province) for an emergency shelter and household NFI support that meet cluster specifications. The project, implemented directly by the Norwegian Refugee Council (NRC), continuing recent and long-standing interventions in these areas, is aligned with the CHF Reserve Strategy Priority B, and has been coordinated through relevant fora, notably the Afghanistan Emergency Shelter and NFI (ES/NFI) Cluster. 

NRC proposes to provide a combination of emergency shelters in the form of in-kind family tents for 1,435 vulnerable families (10,045 individuals) and unconditional cash for NFIs 6,200 AFN (~USD $85 - distribution time market exchange rate to be used) disbursed in two instalments for the same 1,435 drought-displaced families as markets remain functional in target project locations. This will fill existing gaps in ES/ NFI support to the affected population and complement activities currently being undertaken through other funding mechanisms.</narrative>
  </description>
